The paper discusses the feasibility of using mmWave technology for indoor WLANs, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of antenna height, location, orientation, and distance on performance, which relates to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the challenges of human blockage, which relates to augmented reality (cs.AR) and machine learning (cs.MA) in terms of developing algorithms to mitigate the impact of blockage.
